Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Toss potatoes with dressing and pepper in greased 15x10x1-inch baking pan. Spread into single layer. Bake 20 min. Stir in onions. Continue baking 20 min. or until vegetables are tender. Sprinkle with parsley and bacon; stir. Top with cheese. Bake an additional 2 min. or until cheese is melted.